378
00:33:18,280 --> 00:33:20,110
(Ernie) A Jacuzzi tub!

379
00:33:20,200 --> 00:33:22,870
You have to spend money
to make money.

380
00:33:22,950 --> 00:33:25,540
They threw in the cardboard lady too.

381
00:33:28,080 --> 00:33:30,370
(Screaming)

382
00:33:32,380 --> 00:33:34,210
(Screaming)

383
00:33:36,920 --> 00:33:38,840
(Yelling)

384
00:33:41,840 --> 00:33:44,220
(Screaming)

385
00:34:04,780 --> 00:34:07,870
- (Sighing)
- Well...

386
00:34:15,710 --> 00:34:19,300
(Lars sighing) Don't you think
this is a little... much?

387
00:34:19,380 --> 00:34:23,510
Never underestimate your opponent.

388
00:34:23,590 --> 00:34:29,180
Say he has mastered a way to empty
a mousetrap without getting caught.

389
00:34:29,270 --> 00:34:31,640
If he snaps one of these babies,

390
00:34:31,730 --> 00:34:34,940
a chain reaction
will start snapping them all.

391
00:34:35,020 --> 00:34:38,320
The law of averages
says one has to nab him.

392
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:42,360
(Sighs) Not bad.

393
00:34:42,450 --> 00:34:46,200
Yes. Well, I like
to use both sides of my brain.

394
00:34:46,280 --> 00:34:48,160
Come on, let's hit the sack.

395
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:23,400
(Sighing)

396
00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:27,910
- Have you figured it out yet?
- Shut up.

397
00:35:27,990 --> 00:35:30,370
I'm thinking. I'm thinking!

398
00:35:44,090 --> 00:35:46,510
Ernie. Ernie!

399
00:35:50,970 --> 00:35:55,980
Keep perfectly still. This is it.

400
00:36:14,830 --> 00:36:17,210
- What's he doing?
- I don't know.

401
00:36:29,470 --> 00:36:32,010
That was good.

402
00:36:52,790 --> 00:36:55,370
