462
00:41:52,330 --> 00:41:55,460
Yeah! A vicious cat,
difficult to love.

463
00:41:55,550 --> 00:41:58,420
Do you have any of those
knocking around?

464
00:41:58,510 --> 00:42:03,640
Funny you should ask. I had all
but given up on anyone wanting him.

465
00:42:03,720 --> 00:42:06,970
We were about to gas him again.

466
00:42:07,060 --> 00:42:09,100
(Both) Again?

467
00:42:09,180 --> 00:42:12,730
He's spent most of his whole life
in that box, I expect.

468
00:42:12,810 --> 00:42:15,650
- (Growling)
- "Catzilla"?

469
00:42:15,730 --> 00:42:18,070
The guys who clean up call him that.

470
00:42:18,150 --> 00:42:20,860
But you can call him
anything you want.

471
00:42:20,950 --> 00:42:23,240
I'd say he looks like a "Fluffy."

472
00:42:23,320 --> 00:42:26,080
(Snarling)

473
00:42:27,120 --> 00:42:30,500
Ah, poor little Catzilla.

474
00:42:31,540 --> 00:42:35,040
