486
00:43:14,920 --> 00:43:16,840
Yeah, uh, go get 'im, boy.

487
00:43:19,460 --> 00:43:22,010
Oh, easy, easy, easy, easy!

488
00:43:29,890 --> 00:43:33,230
Wow. I almost feel sorry
for the little fella.

489
00:43:34,310 --> 00:43:37,230
(Together) Almost! (Laughs)

490
00:43:38,650 --> 00:43:40,570
(Growling)

491
00:44:04,340 --> 00:44:06,800
(Growling)

492
00:44:06,890 --> 00:44:08,800
(Roaring)

493
00:44:14,940 --> 00:44:17,650
(Meowing)

494
00:44:32,370 --> 00:44:34,750
(Notes playing)

495
00:44:39,670 --> 00:44:41,170
(Cat yowling)

496
00:44:44,130 --> 00:44:46,380
(Ernie) Don't
worry about that mouse,

497
00:44:46,470 --> 00:44:49,010
start thinking about
how to get $1200.

498
00:44:49,090 --> 00:44:52,100
(Lars) Don't worry,
the workers will help us.

499
00:44:52,180 --> 00:44:54,730
You see, the truth is...

500
00:44:55,810 --> 00:44:59,270
- we don't actually have any money.
- (Muttering)

501
00:45:08,740 --> 00:45:12,580
We may have to defer
your next paycheque or... or two.

502
00:45:12,660 --> 00:45:16,290
- (Angry muttering)
- So we can pay the mortgage.

503
00:45:16,410 --> 00:45:18,290
It's the missing LaRue!

504
00:45:18,370 --> 00:45:21,040
(Lars) There's no need
for violence!

505
00:45:23,750 --> 00:45:26,970
(Lars) Put that thing down. Whoa!

506
00:45:36,230 --> 00:45:38,100
(Banging)

507
00:45:46,940 --> 00:45:51,160
- Ernie!
- What's the matter?

508
00:45:51,240 --> 00:45:55,160
Well, the, uh, workers...
didn't react very positively.

509
00:45:55,240 --> 00:45:58,040
(Angry shouting)

510
00:45:58,120 --> 00:45:59,620
No?

511
00:45:59,710 --> 00:46:01,920
Uh, what are you doing?

512
00:46:02,000 --> 00:46:05,670
- You could fit through here, right?
- What? I guess so.

513
00:46:05,750 --> 00:46:07,840
Come on. (Screams)

514
00:46:10,130 --> 00:46:12,470
(Yells)

515
00:46:12,550 --> 00:46:15,310
But, Lars, that was our last resort!

516
00:46:15,390 --> 00:46:18,180
We'll have to
find money someplace else.

517
00:46:36,330 --> 00:46:40,370
Gosh, it's a shame nobody's
interested in buying the factory.

518
00:46:40,460 --> 00:46:44,590
Yeah, yeah, it's a shame.
But who'd be stupid enough, right?

519
00:46:44,670 --> 00:46:47,170
(Chuckling) Yeah.

520
00:46:53,260 --> 00:46:55,640
(Growling)

521
00:47:16,950 --> 00:47:19,200
- (Snap)
- (Yowling)

522
00:47:19,290 --> 00:47:21,210
- (Snapping)
- (Yowling)

523
00:47:38,890 --> 00:47:41,180
(Yowling)

524
00:47:42,600 --> 00:47:44,020
(Growling)

525
00:47:58,910 --> 00:48:01,330
(Surprised meow)

526
00:48:07,170 --> 00:48:09,420
(Sad meow)

527
00:48:31,570 --> 00:48:35,110
Ah, you must be... Caesar.

528
00:48:35,200 --> 00:48:38,030
I'm glad you could get here
so quickly...

529
00:48:38,120 --> 00:48:39,950
Shh!

530
00:48:54,840 --> 00:48:56,930
(Tapping echoes)

531
00:49:05,980 --> 00:49:07,900
(Sniffs)

532
00:49:10,860 --> 00:49:12,480
You have mice.

533
00:49:14,530 --> 00:49:16,450
He's good.

534
00:49:16,530 --> 00:49:19,320
(Whispering) 5120 Nortondale.

535
00:49:19,410 --> 00:49:21,450
January 4th, 0800 hours.

536
00:49:21,530 --> 00:49:24,660
Don't forget to get
toothpaste and Saran Wrap.

537
00:49:24,750 --> 00:49:28,750
We're in sort of a hurry. I wanted
to warn you about this mouse.


